output.analysis:
Let's analyze this post according to the given criteria:
1. Has CMF: Yes, contains "CMF: 11240015" 2. Refers to candidate: Yes, mentions Marcel Ciolacu and Nicolae Ciucă directly, who are presidential candidates 3. Addresses wide population: Yes, this is a paid post on Facebook with significant reach (3,000-3,999 impressions) 4. Electoral objective: Yes, clearly aims to influence voting behavior with statements like "Ai ocazia să-i lași fără putere și fără privilegii. Vino la vot!" 5. Journalism: No, this is not journalistic content but rather political messaging 6. Personal opinion: While containing opinions, this is clearly structured as political messaging with electoral intent
The post directly criticizes PSD-PNL leadership, specifically targeting presidential candidates Marcel Ciolacu and Nicolae Ciucă, while promoting USR's position. It's being promoted after the end of the presidential campaign period, discussing matters related to both parliamentary and presidential elections.

conclusion.electoral-propaganda-analysis: This constitutes electoral propaganda because: - Contains CMF number indicating official campaign material - Directly targets presidential candidates - Has clear electoral objective - Is a paid promotion reaching wide audience - Makes direct calls to voting action
conclusion.message-for-police: Uniunea Salvați România filiala Constanta, pentru incalcarea articolului 55 t) din Legea 370/2004, prin promovarea unui mesaj electoral platit pe Facebook (ID: 914310827466619) dupa incheierea perioadei de campanie electorala pentru alegerile prezidentiale. Postarea contine atacuri directe la adresa candidatilor prezidentiali Marcel Ciolacu si Nicolae Ciucă, cu intenția clara de a influența comportamentul electoral al votanților, fiind distribuită după ora 18:00 pe 23.11.2024. Mesajul include număr CMF (11240015), confirmând natura sa de material de propagandă electorală, și reprezintă o încălcare clară a prevederilor legale privind încetarea campaniei electorale.
